# Cursor chat workflow (zpwi-csid)

**New intent → new chat** (`Ctrl+N` / `Cmd+N`, or the **+** button). Project rules reload automatically; only carry forward what the new task needs.

## Task → chat pattern

### Classify or add a food (research + YAML)

- **Mode:** Agent
- **Attach:** `@data/foods.yaml`
- Research per [project-scope-and-references.mdc](./project-scope-and-references.mdc); cite `sources` on entries when using secondary references.
- After YAML edits, sync lists per [regenerate-all-foods.mdc](./regenerate-all-foods.mdc).

### Sync lists after YAML changes (mechanical)

- **Mode:** Agent
- **Attach:** `@data/foods.yaml` `@.cursor/rules/regenerate-all-foods.mdc`
- Run `python3 scripts/generate-all-foods.py` and `python3 scripts/build-site.py`.
- Hand-update `lists/good-foods.md` and/or `lists/bad-foods.md`; do not hand-edit `lists/all-foods.md`.

### Bulk food import / many entries

- **Mode:** Plan first, then Agent
- **Attach:** `@data/foods.yaml` `@.cursor/rules/project-scope-and-references.mdc`
- Split long work: one chat for research/YAML, a fresh chat for regenerate + good/bad list sync.

### Site / docs styling only

- **Mode:** Agent
- **Attach:** `@docs/` or `@site/` — not `@data/foods.yaml`
- Run `python3 scripts/build-site.py` after HTML/CSS changes.

### Questions only (no edits)

- **Mode:** Ask
- **Attach:** only if you know the file (e.g. `@lists/good-foods.md`).

### Commit / PR

- **Mode:** Agent
- Start a fresh chat; git diff is usually enough context.

## Decision tree

```
What are you doing?
├─ New or changed food in YAML → new chat → classify → regenerate → good/bad lists
├─ YAML already edited, sync only → new chat → regenerate-all-foods rule
├─ Docs/CSS/HTML only → new chat → @docs/ or @site/ → build-site.py
├─ Question, no edits → new chat → Ask mode
└─ Context full or stale assumptions → Ctrl+N + short prompt + @files
```

## Prompt templates

**Single food add:**

> Add [Food name] to data/foods.yaml (status: good|bad, group: …). Follow project-scope-and-references rule. Then sync all lists per regenerate-all-foods rule.

**Sync after YAML edit:**

> foods.yaml is updated. Run generate-all-foods.py and build-site.py. Update good-foods.md / bad-foods.md for: [changes]. Keep comma-grouped format.

**Unrelated task (explicit reset):**

> Ignore prior context. Task: [one sentence]. Files: @path/to/file

## What persists vs clears

| Persists every new chat | Cleared on new chat |
| --- | --- |
| `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, skills, MCP, indexing | Conversation history, tool results, @ chips |
